<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1226&amp;p=61113#p61113"><![CDATA[
Sure, fsc (color subcarrier) is f/6. But the PPU dot clock is f/4, and the CPU clock is f/12, and you can't skip these dividers without making new CPU and PPU ICs.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri May 07, 2010 11:14 am</p><hr />
