<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1226&amp;p=10850#p10850"><![CDATA[
Does the board tap the system's clock? Was the system NTSC in the first place? You probably have a 60hz NTSC unit which does transcode video to 50hz PAL-M, I have an unlicensed replacement PAL transcoder for NTSC Famicom which does this and presumably outputs PAL-I. If thats the case, you can just remove the board as long as it doesn't intercept anything from the main board (as my Famicom does) BTW, does the addon board contain a large DIP IC?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Wed Mar 15, 2006 4:25 pm</p><hr />
